# Judicial Precinct Master Plan Tender Notification

## Notice Details

* **Reference Number**: WS3801944490
* **Notice Date**: January 5, 2023
* **Tender Closing Date**: Thursday, March 3, 2023, 2:00 PM EST
* **Financial and Non-Financial Closes**: Thursday, March 3, 2023, at 2:00 PM EST
* **Expected Contract Start Date**: N/A
* **Expected Contract End Date**: March 31, 2025

## Project Overview

The Department of Public Works and Government Services (PSPC) invites tenders for a Judicial Precinct Master Plan consultation to support planning and preliminary project development initiatives for the Judicial Precinct campus Master Plan. The Master Plan development, including a phased long-term accommodation strategy, calls for a coordinated, digitally enabled, and integrated approach to design and development.

The selected consultant will provide a range of architectural, urban planning, design, engineering, and specialized services to PSPC. The work location is along Wellington Street/Judicial Precinct in Ottawa, ON.

## Eligibility Criteria

Bidders must confirm at the time of submittal of their tender that they are aware of the requirement to provide proof of language proficiency and meet other mandatory language requirements, as outlined in the solicitation document.

## Solicitation Instructions

* All tender documents for this solicitation are available at the contracting authority's website at [insert URL] 
* Bidders must register with the contracting authority before submitting a Proposal.
* Tenders must be submitted electronically, through the contracting authority's e-submission system, at least 7 days prior to the closing time.

## Trade Agreements

This tender solicitation acknowledges Canada-EU Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement (CETA), Canada-Peru Free Trade Agreement (CPFTA), Canada-Panama Free Trade Agreement, North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA), Canadian Free Trade Agreement (CFTA), Canada-UK Trade Continuity Agreement (Canada-UK TCA), Canada-Honduras Free Trade Agreement, Canada-Korea Free Trade Agreement (CKFTA), Canada-Chile Free Trade Agreement (CCFTA), Comprehensive and Progressive Agreement for Trans-Pacific Partnership (CPTPP), World Trade Organization Agreement on Government Procurement (WTO GPA), Canada-Colombia Free Trade Agreement, and Canada-Ukraine Free Trade Agreement (CUFTA).
